          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        <date>Monday Feb. 10 '51</date>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Rev. Mr. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">This day I received the Oc.<lb/> for this month. I
                                        have the request to make of you<lb/> that if you can find it
                                        convenient, you will ad-<lb/>mit my reply to the Jewish
                                        Layman in the <date>March</date><lb/> No. I do not intend to
                                        ask you to admit any reply<lb/> from me to <persName>Dr.
                                                  Wise's</persName> last letter as I hope to
                                        have<lb/> his letter printed in a Presbyterian Paper along
                                        with a<lb/> reply from myself. I have not yet obtained an
                                        absolute<lb/> promise, but I feel pretty sure that his
                                        letter and my re-<lb/>ply will appear in the
                                                  <date>April</date> No. of the House and<lb/>
                                        Foreign Record of the Presbyterian Church. So if you<lb/>
                                        will be so good and publish my reply to the Layman,<lb/> we
                                        will have every thing squared up in this volume<lb/> of the
                                        Occident.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The articles of my opponents have taken up
                                        much<lb/> more space than my letters. For these and other
                                        reasons,<lb/> I hope you will <sic>will</sic> square me up
                                        for this volume,<lb/> and the policy for the next volume may
                                        attend to itself.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Yours most respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">M. R.
                                        Miller</persName>.</p>
                              <p>P. S. Should it involve additional expense to put in my reply
                                        along<lb/> with the other articles which you wish to
                                        publish, I will</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>clear the expense. Please remember that I am not a<lb/> Dr. I hope
                                        you will omit this term which makes me<lb/> appear
                                        ridiculous</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">M.R.M.</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <hi rend="underline">Paid 5 Cent</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>371 Walnut street</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia Pa.</placeName>
                              </p>
